						<div class="postbody">By the way, <a href="https://wiki.nesdev.com/" class="postlink">https://wiki.nesdev.com/</a> appears to redirect to <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Nesdev_Wiki" class="postlink">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Nesdev_Wiki</a>, which seems like a problem for users that are trying to use HTTPS.<br /><br />There's probably a bunch of places on this site that hop from HTTPS to HTTP... I imagine this is a pain to do consistently if you're not just always redirecting to HTTPS.<br /><br /><br />Don't feel like I'm pushing for HTTPS here. I'd prefer to be using it, personally, but please just do whatever you think is best for the site. I was OK with it being HTTP in the past, and I'd be OK with that in the future too. (It's obviously an administration hassle.)</div>

